⏱️ Realistic Time Breakdown (Fresher Roadmap)
📌 Week 1–2 → Core QA Concepts
SDLC, STLC
Testing types (Functional, Regression, Smoke)
Bug Life Cycle
Black Box Testing

👉 Time: 10–14 days
👉 Goal: Understand how testing works in real projects

📌 Week 3 → Manual Testing Practice
Writing Test Cases & Test Scenarios
Finding bugs in sample websites
Practicing edge cases

👉 Time: 5–7 days
👉 Goal: Think like a tester (this is very important)

📌 Week 4 → Tools + Basic Tech
Learn JIRA (bug reporting)
Learn Postman basics
Learn SQL basics (SELECT, WHERE, JOIN)

👉 Time: 7–10 days
👉 Goal: Become job-ready for fresher roles

📌 Week 5–6 (Optional but Powerful 🚀)
Basics of Selenium
Basic Java / JavaScript
API testing deeper concepts

👉 Time: 10–15 days
👉 Goal: Stand out from other freshers

📊 Final Timeline Summary
Basic Job-Ready QA Skills: → 4 weeks
Strong Fresher Profile: → 6–8 weeks
⚠️ Important Reality Check

Many people learn theory fast, but fail in interviews because:

They can’t write test cases properly
They don’t know real-world scenarios
They can’t explain clearly

👉 So focus on:

Practice on real websites (Amazon, Flipkart, etc.)
Write test cases daily
Try to find real bugs
💡 Smart Strategy (What actually works)

Instead of only studying:

Pick 1 website
Test it like a QA engineer
Write:
Test cases
Bug reports
API checks
